00:12:35.150 --> 00:12:36.856 align:middle line:90%
to attend their seances.

00:12:36.856 --> 00:12:38.230 align:middle line:84%
And I think she
probably thought,

00:12:38.230 --> 00:12:42.215 align:middle line:84%
this would be some place where
they might find me interesting.

00:12:42.215 --> 00:12:43.145 align:middle line:90%
And they did.

00:12:43.145 --> 00:12:47.340 align:middle line:90%


00:12:47.340 --> 00:12:50.220 align:middle line:84%
>>Upon her arrival in
New York, Blavatsky

00:12:50.220 --> 00:12:52.080 align:middle line:90%
was virtually penniless.

00:12:52.080 --> 00:12:54.970 align:middle line:10%
She had occasional
income from the family,

00:12:54.970 --> 00:12:56.680 align:middle line:10%
but she had to work.

00:12:56.680 --> 00:13:00.430 align:middle line:10%
She worked making artificial
flowers in a factory.

00:13:00.430 --> 00:13:02.950 align:middle line:84%
>>She was looking
for a way that she

00:13:02.950 --> 00:13:07.350 align:middle line:84%
could continue to survive
when she read in the paper

00:13:07.350 --> 00:13:13.380 align:middle line:84%
stories written by a
man named Henry Olcott.

00:13:13.380 --> 00:13:16.760 align:middle line:84%
>>Henry Steel Olcott
was a respected member

00:13:16.760 --> 00:13:18.740 align:middle line:90%
of New York society.

00:13:18.740 --> 00:13:20.710 align:middle line:10%
He had worked for the
"New York Tribune,"

00:13:20.710 --> 00:13:22.740 align:middle line:10%
was a special
investigator on corruption

00:13:22.740 --> 00:13:26.090 align:middle line:10%
during the Civil War, and was
one of a three-member panel

00:13:26.090 --> 00:13:28.770 align:middle line:10%
appointed to investigate the
assassination of President

00:13:28.770 --> 00:13:30.890 align:middle line:10%
Lincoln.

00:13:30.890 --> 00:13:33.780 align:middle line:84%
He was also a lawyer with a
prosperous business in New York

00:13:33.780 --> 00:13:35.270 align:middle line:90%
City.

00:13:35.270 --> 00:13:38.600 align:middle line:84%
With a lingering interest in
spiritualism from his youth,

00:13:38.600 --> 00:13:41.520 align:middle line:84%
Olcott decided to investigate
some intriguing spirit

00:13:41.520 --> 00:13:43.440 align:middle line:84%
manifestations
that were occurring

00:13:43.440 --> 00:13:46.570 align:middle line:90%
at a farmhouse in Vermont.

00:13:46.570 --> 00:13:49.000 align:middle line:84%
Convinced of the
validity of the spirits,

00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:50.700 align:middle line:84%
he wrote an account
of his observations

00:13:50.700 --> 00:13:52.720 align:middle line:90%
for the New York papers.

00:13:52.720 --> 00:13:54.299 align:middle line:84%
He then headed back
to the farmhouse

00:13:54.299 --> 00:13:55.840 align:middle line:84%
to investigate the
phenomena further.

00:13:55.840 --> 00:13:58.410 align:middle line:90%


00:13:58.410 --> 00:14:02.360 align:middle line:84%
>>It was a farm run by two
brothers named Eddy-- the Eddy

00:14:02.360 --> 00:14:04.190 align:middle line:90%
brothers, who were mediums.

00:14:04.190 --> 00:14:06.340 align:middle line:84%
And they were giving
these seances.

00:14:06.340 --> 00:14:09.460 align:middle line:84%
People from New York or
wherever would come up.

00:14:09.460 --> 00:14:10.670 align:middle line:90%
They would stay there.

00:14:10.670 --> 00:14:11.760 align:middle line:90%
They had room and board.

00:14:11.760 --> 00:14:16.510 align:middle line:84%
And in the evening, they
could attend the performances.

00:14:16.510 --> 00:14:20.040 align:middle line:84%
>>Their home became a gathering
place for spiritualists

00:14:20.040 --> 00:14:22.480 align:middle line:90%
to witness physical phenomena.

00:14:22.480 --> 00:14:29.310 align:middle line:84%
So entities would appear
and walk around the room,

00:14:29.310 --> 00:14:34.260 align:middle line:84%
and be touched by the
persons in attendance.

00:14:34.260 --> 00:14:37.230 align:middle line:84%
The heyday of
spiritualism involved

00:14:37.230 --> 00:14:40.170 align:middle line:84%
physical manifestations,
and the Eddy brothers

00:14:40.170 --> 00:14:43.793 align:middle line:84%
were famous for
providing a plethora

00:14:43.793 --> 00:14:47.305 align:middle line:84%
of unusual and
fascinating appearances.

00:14:47.305 --> 00:14:52.060 align:middle line:90%


00:14:52.060 --> 00:14:54.680 align:middle line:84%
>>Madame Blavatsky was
intrigued both by a desire

00:14:54.680 --> 00:14:58.330 align:middle line:84%
to continue her investigation
into spiritualist phenomena,

00:14:58.330 --> 00:15:02.442 align:middle line:84%
and perhaps to meet the author
of these interesting articles.

00:15:02.442 --> 00:15:05.870 align:middle line:84%
>>She was driven by
the desire for fame

00:15:05.870 --> 00:15:08.545 align:middle line:84%
constantly, even when it
was not in her interest

00:15:08.545 --> 00:15:10.766 align:middle line:84%
to thrust herself
into the headlines.

00:15:10.766 --> 00:15:13.720 align:middle line:90%


00:15:13.720 --> 00:15:16.685 align:middle line:84%
>>So she was at this
Eddy Brother's farm.

00:15:16.685 --> 00:15:19.440 align:middle line:90%


00:15:19.440 --> 00:15:25.010 align:middle line:84%
>>According to Olcott, HPB
certainly stood out in a crowd.

00:15:25.010 --> 00:15:28.850 align:middle line:84%
"My eye was first attracted by
a scarlet, Garibaldian shirt

00:15:28.850 --> 00:15:33.480 align:middle line:84%
she wore, as in vivid contrast
with the dull colors around.

00:15:33.480 --> 00:15:36.810 align:middle line:84%
Her hair was a thick
blond mop worn shorter

00:15:36.810 --> 00:15:39.550 align:middle line:84%
than the shoulders, and it
stood out from her head,

00:15:39.550 --> 00:15:42.830 align:middle line:84%
silken soft and
crinkled to the roots.

00:15:42.830 --> 00:15:46.340 align:middle line:84%
I whispered to my
companion, good gracious,

00:15:46.340 --> 00:15:50.310 align:middle line:84%
look at that
specimen, will you?"

00:15:50.310 --> 00:15:53.030 align:middle line:84%
Olcott recalled that Madame
Blavatsky went outside

00:15:53.030 --> 00:15:54.880 align:middle line:90%
and rolled herself a cigarette.

00:15:54.880 --> 00:15:58.271 align:middle line:84%
He walked over to her and
said, [SPEAKING FRENCH],

00:15:58.271 --> 00:16:01.710 align:middle line:90%
and offered her a light.

00:16:01.710 --> 00:16:04.832 align:middle line:84%
Later, he said that their
acquaintance began in smoke,

00:16:04.832 --> 00:16:09.050 align:middle line:84%
but it stirred up a
great and permanent fire.

00:16:09.050 --> 00:16:10.540 align:middle line:84%
>>He thought she
was fascinating.

00:16:10.540 --> 00:16:15.870 align:middle line:84%
She told him all stories about
being wounded with Garibaldi,

00:16:15.870 --> 00:16:18.330 align:middle line:84%
and she had on kind
of beatnik clothes.

00:16:18.330 --> 00:16:20.050 align:middle line:90%
She wasn't unattractive.

00:16:20.050 --> 00:16:23.880 align:middle line:84%
She was not as obese as
she became later in life,

00:16:23.880 --> 00:16:28.640 align:middle line:84%
but she was a nice
looking, middle aged

00:16:28.640 --> 00:16:32.674 align:middle line:84%
woman who was
dressed peculiarly.

00:16:32.674 --> 00:16:35.090 align:middle line:84%
He thought she was the most
fascinating person he had ever

00:16:35.090 --> 00:16:37.300 align:middle line:90%
met.

00:16:37.300 --> 00:16:39.840 align:middle line:84%
>>Not only was all Olcott's
first meeting with Blavatsky

00:16:39.840 --> 00:16:42.000 align:middle line:84%
memorable, but
the manifestations

00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:44.470 align:middle line:84%
they experienced
together at the Eddy Farm

00:16:44.470 --> 00:16:47.860 align:middle line:84%
convinced him of how
extraordinary she us.

00:16:47.860 --> 00:16:50.820 align:middle line:84%
According to HPB, the
spirits they encountered

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:53.470 align:middle line:84%
during their seances
were numerous,

00:16:53.470 --> 00:16:55.080 align:middle line:90%
and many were familiar to her.

00:16:55.080 --> 00:16:58.995 align:middle line:90%


00:16:58.995 --> 00:17:01.190 align:middle line:84%
"There was a
Georgian boy dressed

00:17:01.190 --> 00:17:03.210 align:middle line:84%
in a historical
Caucasian attire.

00:17:03.210 --> 00:17:05.329 align:middle line:84%
I recognized and
questioned in Georgian

00:17:05.329 --> 00:17:07.960 align:middle line:84%
upon circumstances
known only to myself.

00:17:07.960 --> 00:17:11.619 align:middle line:90%
I was understood and answered."

00:17:11.619 --> 00:17:13.119 align:middle line:90%
"A little old man appears.

00:17:13.119 --> 00:17:15.710 align:middle line:84%
He's dressed as Persian
merchants generally are.

00:17:15.710 --> 00:17:18.400 align:middle line:84%
His dress is perfect
as a national costume.

00:17:18.400 --> 00:17:21.760 align:middle line:84%
He speaks his name
in a loud whisper.

00:17:21.760 --> 00:17:23.810 align:middle line:84%
It is an old man
whom I and my family

00:17:23.810 --> 00:17:26.380 align:middle line:84%
have known for 20
years at Tiflis.

00:17:26.380 --> 00:17:29.340 align:middle line:84%
He says, half in Georgia
man half in Persian,

00:17:29.340 --> 00:17:31.870 align:middle line:84%
that he has got a big
secret to tell me,

00:17:31.870 --> 00:17:34.620 align:middle line:84%
and comes at three different
times vainly seeking

00:17:34.620 --> 00:17:36.150 align:middle line:90%
to finish his sentence."

00:17:36.150 --> 00:17:38.910 align:middle line:84%
"A man of gigantic
stature emerges forth,

00:17:38.910 --> 00:17:40.470 align:middle line:84%
dressed in the
picturesque attire

00:17:40.470 --> 00:17:42.310 align:middle line:90%
of the warriors of Kurdistan.

00:17:42.310 --> 00:17:45.560 align:middle line:84%
He does not speak, but bows
in the oriental fashion,

00:17:45.560 --> 00:17:47.340 align:middle line:84%
and lifts up his
spear ornamented

00:17:47.340 --> 00:17:49.310 align:middle line:84%
with bright-colored
feathers, shaking

00:17:49.310 --> 00:17:51.570 align:middle line:90%
it-- a token of welcome.

00:17:51.570 --> 00:17:54.440 align:middle line:84%
An old woman appears
with Russian headgear.

00:17:54.440 --> 00:17:56.840 align:middle line:84%
She comes out and
addresses me in Russian,

00:17:56.840 --> 00:18:00.870 align:middle line:84%
calling me by an endearing term
that she used in my childhood.

00:18:00.870 --> 00:18:12.490 align:middle line:84%
I recognize an old servant of my
family, a nurse of my sister."

00:18:12.490 --> 00:18:16.100 align:middle line:84%
Their friendship solidified, and
the two returned to New York.

00:18:16.100 --> 00:18:17.650 align:middle line:10%
Shortly after
their arrival, they

00:18:17.650 --> 00:18:19.900 align:middle line:10%
moved in together--
not as a couple,

00:18:19.900 --> 00:18:23.750 align:middle line:10%
but more as kindred spirits.

00:18:23.750 --> 00:18:25.710 align:middle line:10%
>>That was very unusual.

00:18:25.710 --> 00:18:31.300 align:middle line:10%
There was no sexual contact
with them as far as is known.

00:18:31.300 --> 00:18:35.170 align:middle line:84%
They were like comrades,
or brother and sister,

00:18:35.170 --> 00:18:37.910 align:middle line:90%
or professional colleagues.

00:18:37.910 --> 00:18:40.920 align:middle line:84%
In fact, they liked
each other enormously.

00:18:40.920 --> 00:18:42.880 align:middle line:90%
They got on.

00:18:42.880 --> 00:18:46.530 align:middle line:90%
And there was a great affection.

00:18:46.530 --> 00:18:49.350 align:middle line:84%
>>She only became
a spiritual teacher

00:18:49.350 --> 00:18:54.190 align:middle line:84%
after she made the crucial
connection with Henry Steel

00:18:54.190 --> 00:18:57.810 align:middle line:84%
Olcott, who at the time was
a prominent spiritualist,

00:18:57.810 --> 00:19:00.320 align:middle line:84%
and who became her entre
into the world New York

00:19:00.320 --> 00:19:02.640 align:middle line:90%
spiritualism.

00:19:02.640 --> 00:19:05.400 align:middle line:84%
She begins to write
letters to the editor,

00:19:05.400 --> 00:19:10.000 align:middle line:84%
either defending spiritualists
or attacking their critics,

00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:13.250 align:middle line:84%
making a name for herself in the
spiritualist press where Olcott

00:19:13.250 --> 00:19:17.230 align:middle line:90%
is already fairly well known.

00:19:17.230 --> 00:19:19.950 align:middle line:84%
"I am here in this
country sent by my lodge

00:19:19.950 --> 00:19:22.720 align:middle line:84%
on behalf of truth and
modern spiritualism,

00:19:22.720 --> 00:19:25.370 align:middle line:84%
and it is my most
sacred duty to unveil

00:19:25.370 --> 00:19:28.950 align:middle line:84%
what it is and expose
what it is not.

00:19:28.950 --> 00:19:31.820 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps did I arrive
here 100 years too soon?

00:19:31.820 --> 00:19:34.640 align:middle line:84%
Maybe, and I'm afraid
it is so, for people

00:19:34.640 --> 00:19:41.740 align:middle line:84%
seem to care every day less for
truth, and every more for gold.

00:19:41.740 --> 00:19:45.300 align:middle line:84%
My feeble protest and
endeavors will be of no avail.

00:19:45.300 --> 00:19:48.480 align:middle line:84%
Nevertheless, I am ever
ready for the grand battle,

00:19:48.480 --> 00:19:51.330 align:middle line:84%
and perfectly prepared to
bear any consequences that

00:19:51.330 --> 00:19:57.360 align:middle line:90%
may fall to my lot."

00:19:57.360 --> 00:19:59.320 align:middle line:84%
>>There was a place
that they stayed

00:19:59.320 --> 00:20:03.460 align:middle line:84%
called the lamasery,
in which Blavatsky

00:20:03.460 --> 00:20:07.850 align:middle line:84%
had an apartment loaded
with some of her collections

00:20:07.850 --> 00:20:10.280 align:middle line:90%
from India and elsewhere.

00:20:10.280 --> 00:20:13.650 align:middle line:84%
And she would hold
soirees and tell stories.

00:20:13.650 --> 00:20:16.790 align:middle line:10%
And she very quickly
became very well known

00:20:16.790 --> 00:20:20.540 align:middle line:10%
amongst the elite and
the intellectuals.

00:20:20.540 --> 00:20:23.740 align:middle line:84%
>>Blavatsky starts
to become a book

00:20:23.740 --> 00:20:25.820 align:middle line:84%
author in our her
own right, slowly

00:20:25.820 --> 00:20:29.563 align:middle line:84%
beginning to work on what
become "Isis Unveiled."

00:20:29.563 --> 00:20:32.690 align:middle line:84%
>>This was HPB's
first major work,

00:20:32.690 --> 00:20:35.440 align:middle line:84%
and offers her insights on
both Eastern and Western

00:20:35.440 --> 00:20:38.910 align:middle line:90%
religion and philosophy.

00:20:38.910 --> 00:20:42.880 align:middle line:84%
>>Olcott was her collaborator
in the writing process, which

00:20:42.880 --> 00:20:46.680 align:middle line:84%
involved many strange
phenomena, which convinced him

00:20:46.680 --> 00:20:51.660 align:middle line:84%
that she was being assisted
by invisible helpers,

00:20:51.660 --> 00:20:56.990 align:middle line:84%
not only in the spirit world
but living men elsewhere

00:20:56.990 --> 00:20:59.350 align:middle line:84%
who were communicating
telepathically

00:20:59.350 --> 00:21:03.679 align:middle line:84%
or occupying her body,
and writing through her.

00:21:03.679 --> 00:21:07.900 align:middle line:90%


00:21:07.900 --> 00:21:10.590 align:middle line:84%
>>Blavatsky explained that
these invisible helpers

00:21:10.590 --> 00:21:13.130 align:middle line:84%
were adepts or
masters who were part

00:21:13.130 --> 00:21:16.690 align:middle line:84%
of a brotherhood of
enlightened spiritual beings.

00:21:16.690 --> 00:21:19.780 align:middle line:84%
>>Olcott talks about hands
appearing mysteriously

00:21:19.780 --> 00:21:24.450 align:middle line:84%
and writing during the
night while she's asleep.

00:21:24.450 --> 00:21:28.260 align:middle line:84%
The composition process
of "Isis Unveiled"

00:21:28.260 --> 00:21:33.330 align:middle line:84%
is only the first instance
where the authorship of items

00:21:33.330 --> 00:21:37.810 align:middle line:84%
that appear under her
name is somewhat confused,

00:21:37.810 --> 00:21:40.980 align:middle line:84%
because both she and
Olcott say that there were

00:21:40.980 --> 00:21:44.290 align:middle line:84%
many others helping
behind the scenes.

00:21:44.290 --> 00:21:46.110 align:middle line:10%
>>She started writing,
and she said, well,

00:21:46.110 --> 00:21:48.150 align:middle line:10%
I get it from my masters.

00:21:48.150 --> 00:21:49.860 align:middle line:10%
They're dictating to me.

00:21:49.860 --> 00:21:54.080 align:middle line:10%
Or I see it in the astral
light, the inner worlds.

00:21:54.080 --> 00:21:58.580 align:middle line:84%
And I remember when I first read
that, I said, oh yeah, right.

00:21:58.580 --> 00:22:02.510 align:middle line:84%
And I found myself very soon
running back for a glossary

00:22:02.510 --> 00:22:04.730 align:middle line:84%
because the terminology
was a huge barrier.

00:22:04.730 --> 00:22:06.980 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know what all
this Eastern philosophical

00:22:06.980 --> 00:22:08.640 align:middle line:90%
terminology meant.

00:22:08.640 --> 00:22:10.890 align:middle line:84%
And yet, here was a
person who was touching

00:22:10.890 --> 00:22:13.610 align:middle line:84%
every conceivable
subject of importance

00:22:13.610 --> 00:22:18.030 align:middle line:84%
in areas of religion and
philosophy and science,

00:22:18.030 --> 00:22:21.170 align:middle line:90%
written with knowledge.

00:22:21.170 --> 00:22:23.860 align:middle line:84%
And I said, how can a
person know so much about so

00:22:23.860 --> 00:22:30.290 align:middle line:84%
many things, and handle
it with skill in this way?

00:22:30.290 --> 00:22:32.403 align:middle line:90%
I just didn't know.

00:22:32.403 --> 00:22:38.060 align:middle line:84%
>>HPB communicated mainly with
two masters-- Morya and Koot

00:22:38.060 --> 00:22:39.350 align:middle line:90%
Hoomi.

00:22:39.350 --> 00:22:43.200 align:middle line:84%
>>These people lived in Tibet,
but they weren't Tibetans.

00:22:43.200 --> 00:22:45.050 align:middle line:90%
They were Indians.

00:22:45.050 --> 00:22:49.800 align:middle line:84%
And the Brotherhood had picked
her to disseminate their ideas,

00:22:49.800 --> 00:22:51.980 align:middle line:84%
as much as they want
to reveal to the world,

00:22:51.980 --> 00:22:52.990 align:middle line:90%
through the Madame.

00:22:52.990 --> 00:22:56.430 align:middle line:90%


00:22:56.430 --> 00:22:58.750 align:middle line:84%
>>They feel they can
do more for the world

00:22:58.750 --> 00:23:01.310 align:middle line:84%
by not being visible
personalities.

00:23:01.310 --> 00:23:05.070 align:middle line:84%
And there has been a lot
of interesting developments

00:23:05.070 --> 00:23:08.280 align:middle line:84%
of that idea where one hears
about descended masters and so

00:23:08.280 --> 00:23:09.930 align:middle line:90%
forth.

00:23:09.930 --> 00:23:14.130 align:middle line:84%
They themselves say, no,
no, we're fully physical.

00:23:14.130 --> 00:23:17.200 align:middle line:84%
We are what we are by
virtue of our training.

00:23:17.200 --> 00:23:20.710 align:middle line:84%
We have spent our
lifetime pursuing

00:23:20.710 --> 00:23:26.470 align:middle line:84%
spiritual and philosophical
and scientific questions,

00:23:26.470 --> 00:23:31.120 align:middle line:84%
and we feel that we have some
answers that we can provide

00:23:31.120 --> 00:23:35.650 align:middle line:84%
that help humanity to
understand what they are,

00:23:35.650 --> 00:23:37.240 align:middle line:84%
where they came
from-- the answers

00:23:37.240 --> 00:23:40.670 align:middle line:84%
to the questions of
ultimate concern.

00:23:40.670 --> 00:23:44.350 align:middle line:84%
>>These masters are more
spiritually evolved.

00:23:44.350 --> 00:23:48.840 align:middle line:10%
That means that they can live
longer-- hundreds of years--

00:23:48.840 --> 00:23:52.430 align:middle line:10%
they have much more
knowledge, they

00:23:52.430 --> 00:24:00.320 align:middle line:10%
are almost-- if you can use
an analogy, almost resembling,

00:24:00.320 --> 00:24:03.410 align:middle line:10%
we might say, the
hidden hand theory,

00:24:03.410 --> 00:24:06.810 align:middle line:10%
which means that
behind this world,

00:24:06.810 --> 00:24:09.650 align:middle line:10%
there is a small
cadre of individuals

00:24:09.650 --> 00:24:11.870 align:middle line:10%
who are controlling things.

00:24:11.870 --> 00:24:17.990 align:middle line:10%
And so these masters are in
separate brotherhoods in India,

00:24:17.990 --> 00:24:23.790 align:middle line:10%
in Egypt, and elsewhere who
are helping to perhaps control

00:24:23.790 --> 00:24:27.360 align:middle line:10%
the progress of the planet
and spreading the wisdom.

