of this kind, and
many theosophists

00:37:31.110 --> 00:37:34.870 align:middle line:84%
were concerned about
his lack of experience.

00:37:34.870 --> 00:37:38.150 align:middle line:84%
After months of what he felt
was careful investigation,

00:37:38.150 --> 00:37:41.810 align:middle line:84%
he concluded that there was no
secret brotherhood of masters,

00:37:41.810 --> 00:37:47.330 align:middle line:84%
and all the correspondence from
the Mahatmas was fraudulent.

00:37:47.330 --> 00:37:51.030 align:middle line:10%
>>The Hodgson Report
forever condemned

00:37:51.030 --> 00:37:55.740 align:middle line:10%
Blavatsky in terms of
general public perception

00:37:55.740 --> 00:38:00.620 align:middle line:10%
by words that have been repeated
many times ever since that one.

00:38:00.620 --> 00:38:03.285 align:middle line:84%
One of the most ingenious
and accomplished impostors

00:38:03.285 --> 00:38:03.785 align:middle line:90%
in history.

00:38:03.785 --> 00:38:07.440 align:middle line:90%


00:38:07.440 --> 00:38:09.780 align:middle line:84%
Blavatsky and Olcott
both blamed each other

00:38:09.780 --> 00:38:13.220 align:middle line:84%
for the sensationalism that led
to the investigation, and then

00:38:13.220 --> 00:38:15.730 align:middle line:90%
the negative report.

00:38:15.730 --> 00:38:19.290 align:middle line:84%
So while he was telling her
that her sensationalism had 3/4

00:38:19.290 --> 00:38:20.990 align:middle line:84%
ruined the TS and
another dose would

00:38:20.990 --> 00:38:23.420 align:middle line:84%
kill it deader than
a door nail, she

00:38:23.420 --> 00:38:25.950 align:middle line:84%
was saying that
if Olcott had not

00:38:25.950 --> 00:38:30.860 align:middle line:84%
made such a cult of the masters,
inflaming people's imagination

00:38:30.860 --> 00:38:35.320 align:middle line:84%
with tall tales about them, that
the Indian followers and then

00:38:35.320 --> 00:38:40.480 align:middle line:84%
the Westerners would never have
become so crazed with worship

00:38:40.480 --> 00:38:44.760 align:middle line:84%
of the masters that everything
would have collapsed

00:38:44.760 --> 00:38:48.120 align:middle line:84%
in this embarrassing
humiliation.

00:38:48.120 --> 00:38:50.500 align:middle line:84%
That is what she was
saying, and her quote

00:38:50.500 --> 00:38:54.750 align:middle line:84%
is, "when you speak of
the imaginary Mahatmas,

00:38:54.750 --> 00:38:57.150 align:middle line:90%
you are right."

00:38:57.150 --> 00:38:59.590 align:middle line:84%
But she's not taking
responsibility herself

00:38:59.590 --> 00:39:00.220 align:middle line:90%
at this point.

00:39:00.220 --> 00:39:02.303 align:middle line:84%
She's saying, yes, the
masters have been blown out

00:39:02.303 --> 00:39:05.910 align:middle line:84%
of all proportion, and
theosophist faith is now

00:39:05.910 --> 00:39:09.130 align:middle line:84%
built on a house of sand,
but it's Olcott's fault

00:39:09.130 --> 00:39:12.210 align:middle line:84%
because he fanned the flames
of the sensationalism,

00:39:12.210 --> 00:39:16.160 align:middle line:84%
conveniently forgetting
who caused Olcott to become

00:39:16.160 --> 00:39:18.630 align:middle line:84%
such an enthusiast of the
masters in the first place.

00:39:18.630 --> 00:39:21.460 align:middle line:90%


00:39:21.460 --> 00:39:24.280 align:middle line:84%
The big turning point
in the relationship

00:39:24.280 --> 00:39:28.110 align:middle line:84%
of Olcott and Blavatsky--
if it could be pinpointed

00:39:28.110 --> 00:39:32.500 align:middle line:84%
to a single event-- was
Richard Hodgson showing Olcott

00:39:32.500 --> 00:39:37.470 align:middle line:84%
a letter in which HPB
ridiculed him, and said

00:39:37.470 --> 00:39:40.760 align:middle line:84%
that he was completely
under her sway.

00:39:40.760 --> 00:39:46.300 align:middle line:84%
She treated his belief in
her as an object of contempt.

00:39:46.300 --> 00:39:49.290 align:middle line:84%
And he said, after reading that,
he was completely distraught

00:39:49.290 --> 00:39:51.900 align:middle line:90%
and contemplated suicide.

00:39:51.900 --> 00:39:55.580 align:middle line:84%
Olcott begins to question
what he's experienced,

00:39:55.580 --> 00:40:01.150 align:middle line:84%
and to say that sometimes she
was deliberately misleading,

00:40:01.150 --> 00:40:04.050 align:middle line:84%
sometimes the phenomena
were not genuine.

00:40:04.050 --> 00:40:07.655 align:middle line:84%
He however never goes
so far as to clue

00:40:07.655 --> 00:40:10.011 align:middle line:84%
that everything he's
experienced was trickery.

00:40:10.011 --> 00:40:13.020 align:middle line:90%


00:40:13.020 --> 00:40:15.570 align:middle line:84%
At the time, the Hodgson
Report was a scandal

00:40:15.570 --> 00:40:17.570 align:middle line:90%
for the Theosophical Society.

00:40:17.570 --> 00:40:21.320 align:middle line:84%
100 years later, the Society
of Psychical Research

00:40:21.320 --> 00:40:24.020 align:middle line:84%
formally acknowledged that
the original report was

00:40:24.020 --> 00:40:27.720 align:middle line:84%
badly flawed, and there was
still many unanswered questions

00:40:27.720 --> 00:40:30.900 align:middle line:84%
concerning the life and
work of Madame Blavatsky.

00:40:30.900 --> 00:40:33.545 align:middle line:90%


00:40:33.545 --> 00:40:35.930 align:middle line:90%
But the damage was done.

00:40:35.930 --> 00:40:42.220 align:middle line:84%
In with a heavy heart,
HPB left India for good.

00:40:42.220 --> 00:40:45.970 align:middle line:84%
Olcott remained to carry on the
work they had started together.

00:40:45.970 --> 00:40:49.010 align:middle line:84%
With a few stops along
the way, she eventually

00:40:49.010 --> 00:40:52.930 align:middle line:90%
settled down in London.

00:40:52.930 --> 00:40:56.040 align:middle line:84%
"My heart is broken
physically and morally.

00:40:56.040 --> 00:40:57.662 align:middle line:90%
For the first, I do not care."

00:40:57.662 --> 00:40:59.120 align:middle line:84%
"Master shall take
care it does not

00:40:59.120 --> 00:41:01.650 align:middle line:90%
burst so long as I am needed.

00:41:01.650 --> 00:41:04.230 align:middle line:84%
In the second case,
there is no help.

00:41:04.230 --> 00:41:07.530 align:middle line:84%
I was ready to shed the last
drop of life in me, give up

00:41:07.530 --> 00:41:10.260 align:middle line:84%
every hope for the
last shred of-- I

00:41:10.260 --> 00:41:13.600 align:middle line:84%
shall not say happiness-- but
rest and comfort in this life

00:41:13.600 --> 00:41:15.970 align:middle line:84%
of torture of the
cause I serve and

00:41:15.970 --> 00:41:21.750 align:middle line:90%
for every true theosophist."

00:41:21.750 --> 00:41:26.160 align:middle line:84%
She again presided
over a lodge in London

00:41:26.160 --> 00:41:29.920 align:middle line:84%
that was a very hot ticket
to be invited to attend.

00:41:29.920 --> 00:41:31.830 align:middle line:84%
And it was not
simply theosophists

00:41:31.830 --> 00:41:35.810 align:middle line:84%
that came to see her, but
anybody who was interested

00:41:35.810 --> 00:41:38.850 align:middle line:84%
in the subjects
that she discussed,

00:41:38.850 --> 00:41:42.840 align:middle line:84%
and in meeting a very
controversial and intriguing

00:41:42.840 --> 00:41:44.084 align:middle line:90%
figure.

00:41:44.084 --> 00:41:46.577 align:middle line:84%
>>Then in the last
two years of her life,

00:41:46.577 --> 00:41:50.360 align:middle line:84%
she drew the attention of
a well known British woman

00:41:50.360 --> 00:41:51.680 align:middle line:90%
named Annie Besant.

00:41:51.680 --> 00:41:57.150 align:middle line:84%
Annie Besant was a feminist,
a union organizer, a writer,

00:41:57.150 --> 00:42:04.160 align:middle line:84%
a person who was enormously
admired in British society.

00:42:04.160 --> 00:42:07.330 align:middle line:84%
Getting the approval of
a woman like Annie Besant

00:42:07.330 --> 00:42:12.250 align:middle line:84%
brought her an enormous
number of new converts,

00:42:12.250 --> 00:42:16.174 align:middle line:84%
much better press than
she'd ever had before.

00:42:16.174 --> 00:42:19.850 align:middle line:84%
Madame Besant left the
Theosophical Society

00:42:19.850 --> 00:42:22.220 align:middle line:90%
to Annie Besant.

00:42:22.220 --> 00:42:23.690 align:middle line:90%
She turned it over to her.

00:42:23.690 --> 00:42:26.280 align:middle line:84%
And with that, she achieved
the ultimate respectability.

00:42:26.280 --> 00:42:29.240 align:middle line:90%


00:42:29.240 --> 00:42:32.900 align:middle line:84%
>>Her sincerity increased
over the course of her career,

00:42:32.900 --> 00:42:35.850 align:middle line:90%
so she learns from our mistakes.

00:42:35.850 --> 00:42:37.430 align:middle line:84%
And in the last few
years, when she's

00:42:37.430 --> 00:42:39.530 align:middle line:84%
doing most of her
writings, she's

00:42:39.530 --> 00:42:44.400 align:middle line:84%
a much more careful
and responsible person

00:42:44.400 --> 00:42:48.560 align:middle line:84%
than she was when she was in
the throes of propagandizing

00:42:48.560 --> 00:42:50.380 align:middle line:84%
for Theosophical
and the masters,

00:42:50.380 --> 00:42:53.960 align:middle line:84%
and getting herself in
the headlines constantly.

00:42:53.960 --> 00:42:55.430 align:middle line:84%
>>During this
period of her life,

00:42:55.430 --> 00:42:57.950 align:middle line:84%
she wrote "The Secret
Doctrine-- The Synthesis

00:42:57.950 --> 00:43:01.360 align:middle line:84%
